# Miko UI rules

This project renders UI with **Miko** — Razor components compiled and drawn with SkiaSharp. It is **not** the web: no HTML/CSS runtime, styles are C# objects, and only a fixed element set exists.

## Read the reference first

Agent-optimized docs live under `.miko/` at the project root. Entry point: `.miko/llms.txt`.

- `.miko/overview.md` — mental model + hard constraints. Read first.
- `.miko/elements/index.md` — the exact DOM element set (check before using any tag).
- `.miko/components/index.md` — Ionic components + parent/child rules.
- `.miko/styling.md` — the typed `Style` object, `Length`, `Color`, `StyleSheet` + `CssObject`.
- `.miko/layout.md`, `.miko/events.md`, `.miko/razor.md`, `.miko/project.md`.
- `.miko/examples/` — counter / tabs / sidemenu.

## Rules

- **Add a page**: create `Pages/Foo.razor` with `@page "/foo"`. Routes are auto-discovered.
- **Styles are C# objects**, never CSS strings. Use `GlobalStyles.cs` (`StyleSheet` + `CssObject`) or an inline `Style` object. Never write `style="color:red"`.
- **No `inherit` keyword** — set non-inherited properties explicitly.
- **Only listed elements exist.** There is no `<textarea>`, `<form>`, `<header>`, `<section>`, `<em>`, `<br>`, `<hr>`. Use `<div>`/`<span>` (see `.miko/elements/index.md`).
- **Ionic** components require `builder.AddIonic()` + `@using Miko.Ionic.Components`, take a `Style` object (not a string), and follow parent/child rules (e.g. `IonItem` inside `IonList`).
